Class Cell

  • java.lang.Object
    • Cell
  • public class Cell
extends java.lang.Object
    The Cell class creates objects representing the cells that make up each generation in an Elementary Cellular Automata.
    Author:
    Devin McAfee

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field Description
      private int state
      The numerical state of any cell, which can either be 0 or 1.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Cell

        public Cell​(int num)
        Constructor assigning the state field to either 0 or 1 depending on the value of the given int. Returns an error message prompting the user to reconstruct the Cell object if the value of the given int is not 0 or 1 and assigns state to -1.
        Parameters:
        num - an int representing the state of a Cell, which can either be 0 or 1.

      • Cell

        public Cell()
        Default constructor, which should not be used. Prompts the user to use the alternate constructor and assigns state to -1.
